<h1>Help & Documentation</h1>
<h1>THIS PAGE IS SAMPLE TEXT AND NOT ACCURATE</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>
This application runs as a background service that connects to IoT devices over HTTP/IP,
collects telemetry data, and uploads it securely to the cloud via IoT Hub.
</p>

<h2>How It Works</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Discovers or connects to configured IoT devices</li>
    <li>Polls devices at a configured interval</li>
    <li>Processes and formats the data</li>
    <li>Uploads data to the cloud via IoT Hub</li>
</ol>

<h2>Getting Started</h2>

<h3>1. Configure Devices</h3>
<p>Add device IP addresses and endpoints in the configuration.</p>

<h3>2. Set Polling Interval</h3>
<p>Define how often the service should query devices.</p>

<h3>3. Configure Cloud Connection</h3>
<p>Provide your IoT Hub connection string and credentials.</p>

<h3>4. Start the Service</h3>
<p>Run the application and verify connection status.</p>

<h2>Configuration Example</h2>

<pre>
{
  "Devices": [
    { "Ip": "192.168.1.10", "Endpoint": "/api/data" }
  ],
  "PollingIntervalSeconds": 30,
  "IoTHubConnectionString": "..."
}
</pre>
